      "BSEE on-site investigation conducted on 10-APR-2014",
      "G-110 Incident of Non-Compliance issued"
    ],
    "summary": "On April 9, 2014, two Roustabouts on the Nabors Sundowner XIV were injured while transferring barite from a supply boat to the rig's storage tanks. After the Crane Operator instructed the work boat to blow down the fill hose, one Roustabout misheard instructions and began disconnecting the four-inch rubber transfer hose while it was still under pressure. The pressurized hose blew off the connection and struck both workers\u2014one in the back of the neck and one in the lower left leg. Both were medevac'd and received full medical releases.",
